            "answer_text": "My first encounter with the phrase was from a fellow university student sometime between late 1969 and early 1971. He was a brilliant philosophy major who read endlessly on many topics. As I recall, he said he had found a striking phrase in a translation of some German philosopher: \u201cFrom the mouths of cunning linguists flows the spittle of wisdom.\u201d Having little interest in German philosophers at the time, I never asked him to be more specific. I\u2019ve always remembered the sentence, but I have yet to find any reason to insert it in a conversation. I have wondered from time to time if he was mocking a slightly naive undergraduate. ",
